Closely related 2-HPA analogues were selected as follows: hydroxy group missing version of 2-HPA; valeric acid, hydroxy group position altered version; 3-hydroxyvaleric acid, shorter fatty acid chain; 2-hydroxybutyric acid, longer fatty acid chain; 2-hydroxyhexanoic acid, missing double bonded oxygen; 1,2 pentanediol (Fig. 1
                     A). Although no agonistic activity to induce oocyte maturation was observed when incubated compounds alone were incubated with oocytes (data not shown), 2-HPA showed antagonistic activity against DHP-induced oocyte maturation (Fig. 1B). Only 2-HPA showed inhibitory activity on DHP-induced oocyte maturation and its analogues showed no activity (Fig. 1B). The physiological activity of the compounds was further confirmed by an in vivo oocyte maturation and ovulation assay using female zebrafish. Again, only 2-HPA showed inhibitory activity on oocyte maturation and ovulation (Fig. 2
                     ). In addition, 2-HPA contains a chiral center in its structure; thus, we confirmed that two optical isomers are possible for this compound (S & R type 2-HPA) (Fig. 1A). Finally, we compared the activity of the 2-HPA isomers. The results showed that both (R)-2-HPA and (S)-2-HPA inhibited oocyte maturation and ovulation with the same level of activity (Fig. 3
                     ), with (R)-2-HPA and (S)-2-HPA, strongly suggesting that both isomers act as antagonists for mPRα.
